-- Brazilian Stock Movers: BR Malls, Ecorodovias, AES Tiete
-- B y   Z a c h a r y   T r a c e r
-- 2012-01-18T20:46:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-18/brazilian-stock-movers-br-malls-ecorodovias-aes-tiete.html
The following companies had  unusual 
price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading. Preferred
shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The  Bovespa (IBOV)  index rose 1.8 percent to 61,722.86.  BR Malls Participacoes SA (BRML3)  (BRML3 BS) gained 2.2 percent to
18.70 reais. Same-store rental revenue in the fourth quarter
increased at a record pace at  Brazil ’s biggest owner of shopping
malls, according to preliminary results in a filing yesterday.  Ecorodovias Infraestruture e Logistica SA  (ECOR3 BS) fell
5.2 percent, the most in five months, to 12.13 reais. The
roadway operator offered too large a discount to win a contract
to manage a Brazilian highway, according to BTG Pactual SA.  AES Tiete SA (GETI4)  (GETI4 BS) dropped 1.4 percent to 25.15 reais.
The power generator was reduced to “underperform” from
“market perform” at Bradesco Corretora.  To contact the reporter on this story:
